<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Shdennlin's Blog</title><link>https://blog.shdennlin.com/</link><description>Recent content on Shdennlin's Blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 09 May 2022 00:00:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.shdennlin.com/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Prevent SSH from disconnecting from timing out</title><link>https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/prevent-ssh-from-disconnecting-from-timing-out/</link><pubDate>Mon, 09 May 2022 00:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/prevent-ssh-from-disconnecting-from-timing-out/</guid><description>&lt;p>When you use ssh to connect the remote server, but there is no operation for a long time, it&amp;rsquo;s annoying issue that disconnects from timing out.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You can prevent it by adding the following line to your &lt;code>~/.ssh/config&lt;/code> file head.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">Host *
ServerAliveInterval &lt;span class="m">30&lt;/span>
ServerAliveCountMax &lt;span class="m">2&lt;/span>
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>I Hope this can resolve your problem.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Spacemacs - Spell Checking Configuration in Windows</title><link>https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/spacemacs-spell-checking-in-windows/</link><pubDate>Mon, 09 May 2022 00:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/spacemacs-spell-checking-in-windows/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/spacemacs-spell-checking-in-windows/image.jpeg" alt="Featured image of post Spacemacs - Spell Checking Configuration in Windows" />&lt;p>This post will introduce how to install &lt;strong>Spell Checking&lt;/strong> on &lt;a class="link" href="https://develop.spacemacs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>spacemacs&lt;/a> in windows. &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I will use &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/hunspell/hunspell" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>hunspell&lt;/a> instead to &lt;a class="link" href="https://www-sop.inria.fr/members/Manuel.Serrano/flyspell/flyspell.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>flyspell&lt;/a> on windows. &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="install-step">Install Step&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>In spacemacs init.el add &lt;code>spell-checking&lt;/code> layer. &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Download the &lt;a class="link" href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/ezwinports/files/?source=navbar" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>hunspell win32 binairy here&lt;/a>, look for hunspell-1.3.2-3-w32-bin.zip (ex: ctrl+F hunspell) &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Unzip it, and copy to location (ex: &lt;strong>d:\application\hunspell-1.3.2-3-w32-bin\bin\hunspell.exe&lt;/strong>) &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Add this to your init.el file &lt;strong>dotspacemacs/user-config block&lt;/strong>: &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-lisp" data-lang="lisp">&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nv">setq-default&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nv">ispell-program-name&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s">&amp;#34;d:/application/hunspell-1.3.2-3-w32-bin/bin/hunspell.exe&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">)&lt;/span>
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>note that the &lt;strong>\&lt;/strong> have change into &lt;strong>/&lt;/strong>. &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="ref">Ref&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>&lt;a class="link" href="https://emacs.stackexchange.com/a/57842" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>aspell with emacs 26.1 on ms windows&lt;/a> &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol></description></item><item><title>About</title><link>https://blog.shdennlin.com/about/</link><pubDate>Wed, 11 Aug 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.shdennlin.com/about/</guid><description>&lt;p>Hi, I am Shawn, a electrical engineering student at &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.ntut.edu.tw/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>National Taipei University of Technology&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Install GUI in WSL2 using VcXsrv</title><link>https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/install-gui-in-wsl2-using-vcxsrv/</link><pubDate>Wed, 11 Aug 2021 00:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/install-gui-in-wsl2-using-vcxsrv/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/install-gui-in-wsl2-using-vcxsrv/vcxsrv-init-screen.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Install GUI in WSL2 using VcXsrv" />&lt;p>Introduction how to install GUI desktop in WSL2 with VcSxrv in winsows 10.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="install-step">Install Step&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="install-wsl">Install WSL&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>First check if you Windows 10 Version supports WSL 2 or not checkout the &lt;a class="link" href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install-win10" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>Link&lt;/a> and Install.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="download-vcsxrv">Download VcSxrv&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Download X server connected tool, I use &lt;a class="link" href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/vcxsrv/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>VcXsrv&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="update-ubuntu-20-dot-04-to-the-latest-version">Update Ubuntu 20.04 to the latest version&lt;/h3>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get upgrade
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="x-server-vcxsrv-configuration">x-server VcXsrv configuration&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Open the Ubuntu 20.04 LTS terminal and type below to install XFCE4 Desktop:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">$ sudo apt-get install x11-apps
$ sudo apt-get install xfce4
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>When you install xfce4, you maybe need to select the Default Display Manager link this:&lt;br>
&lt;img src="https://blog.shdennlin.com/ox-hugo/change-the-default-display-manager.png"
loading="lazy"
>&lt;br>
If you don&amp;rsquo;t how to select, you can reference &lt;a class="link" href="https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/131496/what-is-lightdm-and-gdm/131497#131497?newreg=7caa2cd48b7b447f8b612ca8a7a13c5a" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>What is LightDM and GDM&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>After the installation finished, open .bashrc add some configuration.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">$ &lt;span class="nb">cd&lt;/span> ~
$ vi .bashrc
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Go to the last line and write this&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="c1"># For WSL2&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="nb">export&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nv">DISPLAY&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>&lt;span class="k">$(&lt;/span>cat /etc/resolv.conf &lt;span class="p">|&lt;/span> grep nameserver &lt;span class="p">|&lt;/span> awk &lt;span class="s1">&amp;#39;{print $2}&amp;#39;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="k">)&lt;/span>:0.0
&lt;span class="nb">export&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nv">LIBGL_ALWAYS_INDIRECT&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>&lt;span class="m">1&lt;/span>
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>and Exit your WSL and run it again.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Now after we got everything we need, let&amp;rsquo;s start the session&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">$ startxfce4
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>and go back you windows to open VcXsrv main program(XLaunch) you can use you GUI in WSL&lt;br>
&lt;img src="https://blog.shdennlin.com/ox-hugo/vcxsrv-init-screen.jpg"
loading="lazy"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Congratulations!! Now you can use your WSL using Graphical User Interface.&lt;/p>
